I had to trick Bandcamp to thinking some of the songs were higher Hz and bitrate to be released by adding white noise for a few seconds at very low volume (-36 dB).
Made from sampling someone playing a Mukkuri and edited in Audacity.

Lord Cernunnos.title: Censored
Lord Cernunnos.about:
Sadly LWN is dead, hopefully just for the time being but who knows. This also means a number of Lord Cernunnos releases and 1 Dc 1057 release are no longer available. So I decided to make this large compilation containing all of my releases on LWN. Many of the tracks on this compilation is music I don't make anymore or music that no longer sounds quite like the music I make now. The music on this compilation ranges from Noise Ambient, Dark Ambient, Noise and Harsh Wall Noise and even a bit of Industrial/Rhythmic Noise under the alias Dc 1057.
Track 1 From "Pantyhose And Panties" LWN85.
Track 2 From "One Year In The Scene!" Various Artist compilation, LWN88.
Track 3 - 7 From "死" LWN98.
Track 8 - 10 From "The 100" Various Artist compilation, LWN100.
Track 11 From "Noise Mutilation" a 8-Way Split, LWN113.
Track 12 From "Loli Christmas 2kX6" Various Artist compilation, LWN118.
Track 13 - 16 From "Meganekko" LWN119.
Track 17 - 22 From "EWII" LWN124.
Track 23 From "A Yandere Valentine's Day" LWN131.
Track 24 - 46 From "23 Tracks" a compilation of mostly previously releases. LWN144.
Track 47 From "Aliens Are Invading Our Planet" LWN155.
Track 48 From "Bound JK" LWN183.
Track 49 - 51 From "Numbers" LWN169. The only release from another alias on LWN.
Most of the artwork from the original releases are included but some from compilations and 1 split release are not included due to the fact that I didn't make them. Most of covers are a bonus item and only available as a whole download. If you want to download individual releases and still have the cover(s) you can download them here:  archive.org/details/LordCernunnosDc1057LWNCovers

Lord Cernunnos.title: Gallarus Oratory
Lord Cernunnos.about:
A short Noise EP.
Domkyrka is the new name for Distorted Faith as it makes more sense for a project exclusively dealing with Christian sites of worship. I want the new project name to clear things up as it was never a anti-Christian or anti-religious project at all despite the confusing old name. The name actually comes from the 1st unreleased track that was a Drone/Noise track made from layered church organs and lots of added effects, so it sounded rather distorted. So the project ended up with a silly name as many project from that time. This was before the 1st release and the theme of Christian sites of worship.
I didn't think much about the name when I restarted the project again as the titles were originally untitled. The theme of Christian sites of worship was inspired by Herukrat's Islamic theme from his album "I Bear Witness" since it was interesting and different theme in noise. I started searching for other religious themes in noise but could not really find any and rename the tracks I was working on after Fantoft Stave Church as I'm interested in Scandinavian themes. Hopefully this clears everything up as I prefer most of my release having little info.

Lord Cernunnos.title: The Internet Won't Take My Love
Lord Cernunnos.about:

trackinfo.title: Sometimes The Information We See Online Should Be Taken With A Few Grains Of Salt
trackinfo.about:
The non tl;dr version.
And by love I mean the FLAC files that I saved in weird/improper settings, the files were saved with a Header set as Raw (header-less) and with the encoding set as Unsigned 8-bit PCM and saved as a FLAC file by adding .flac to the end of the file name. When I tested uploading the 1st track to Archive, Archive basically treated the file as a movie file. Bandcamp will act like it's a file with the wrong settings or the like. Audacity would not open it like it does with most music files (or the ones I've used at least) and it had to be opened as raw data. Luckily opening it as raw data seems to either do nothing or be the thing that causes it to have lo-fi static sounds and other minor changes.

Lord Cernunnos.title: Unobtainium
Lord Cernunnos.about:
The only music contained in this EP is in the form of a text file. The only known way to properly listen to this track is to open with notepad++ (might be possible with other similar text editors) and save as a music file instead of a txt file. And It still needs to be opened in Audacity and re-saved. Wordpad will still work but it will alter the sound and has to still be opened in Audacity anyway. But in this case it would have to be opened as raw data. I should note that this version is also a lot louder by default vs the version that is meant to be heard. It's possible neither fix will sound the same as it does for me and also possible that it won't even work.
I also should note that notepad++ isn't the same as notepad and I'm unsure if it's even possible to get the track working using notepad.
Musically this started off as a slowed down pink noise. It was then corrupted in notepad++. This is were all the distortion and other sounds were created.
The Intro track is completely silent.
i like to keep my duke nukem installation floppies attached to my computer with magnets so i don't lose them.
